<br>
I must inform all of you that it may be a bit difficult to find me for the next few days/weeks however long it takes.<br>
<br>
I recieved some information while hunting in the Lake of Ill Omen that my mother had been seen passing through with my father many years ago.  They had said they were on their way to Warslik Woods to visit the local Giant tribe.  The informant snickered and conitnued by telling me that they must have gotten quite a surprise, the giants there are not friendly. and dont speak any language that he knew of beyond grunts and belches.  <br>
<br>
His words made me curious and a bit angry at the possibility of these Giant men causing harm to my peaceful family.<br>
<br>
So i am off in search of these Giants and will return when i feel i have learned all i can from them.  <br>
<br>
Safe journey's to you all.<br>
<br>
Salvia Mirasdottir<br>
24th lvl druid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/usolarianne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Solarianne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/20/01 12:32:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Hail Salvia,<br>
<br>
     Alas, it may distress you greatly to hear these words, but it is, I think, in the best interest of any traveler to heed them.<br>
<br>
     The Warsliks Woods are filled with many wandering dangers, in addition to the giants which have built their fort there, including goblins, hairy apelike brutes, and Iksar. Be most careful when traveling through this area.<br>
<br>
     Perhaps your parents may have been taken prisoner by one of the brutes. I hear that they often capture unwary travelers from the woods, and bring them to their master in the crypt of Dalnir, to act as unwilling servants.<br>
<br>
     It may be that some information regarding their whereabouts may be gained from those who still labor against their will in Dalnir.<br>
<br>
Best of luck to you in your Quest, Salvia.<br>
Please let us know if we can be of any assistance.<br>
<br>
Yours in the Light,<br>
Solarianne Starforge<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/20/01 1:12:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> A Scribe writes:<br>
<br>
Salvia,<br>
<br>
I have recently been in the Crypt of Dalnir, and in fact am having this written to you from that vicinity.  In my travels there, I have not yet seen any Coerced Wood Elves.  The Kly seems to favor Gnomes, Dwarves, Erudites, Goblins, Iksar, and Teir'Dal as slaves.  <br>
<br>
Nay, your parents have not been found in that evil Crypt.  I fear for them being there, as the only release I am aware of for the Coerced Ones is death.  I do not know of any who can undo the effects of coersion, or whether such a thing can be accomplished.  <br>
<br>
O! That they might be found elsewhere and again see our happy woods in Faydwer.<br>
<br>
My blade is at your service in this task.  Call upon me as you have need.<br>
<br>
Tigonie Silvanstar<br>
Warrior of the 35th Season <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/20/01 8:22:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Thank you for the information and kind words Tigonie.<br>
<br>
I have spent a fortnight killing Giants in frontier mountains with other members of the guild and I think I am ready to travel to Warslik Woods in search of any answers I can find.<br>
<br>
I was lucky enough to acquire a map of the wodds and should be able to make my way around easily..I have a good sense of direction a trait of my father I hear.<br>
<br>
Wish me luck all....I will need it<br>
<br>
Signed,<br>
Salvia Mirasdottir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 4:14:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> A Scribe Writes:<br>
<br>
Salvia,<br>
<br>
If you would like to venture into the Crypt yourself, this could be accomplished by your 27th or 28th Season.  I intend to venture back soon (/ooc when I am online the next time after the Aide Station, probably Sunday) and would be pleased if you would join me. We shall be within 10 seasons of each other and should both gain in skills.  I would very much enjoy the company.<br>
<br>
Tigonie Silvanstar<br>
Warrior of the 35th Season <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 8:57:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Salvia,<br>
   If you have found that you can manage the Giants in the Frontier mountians, then the giants in the Warslicks Woods should be no problem. The breed there are weaker for the most parts. I believe you will find that the Goblins and Iksar of WW are a bit tougher than the giants, but still very manageable. Brutes and their kin are generally non-agressive, although the pretty much hate everyone.<br>
   The Crypt of Dalnir is the location of great treasure, as well as some serious hazards. I would highly recommend a group of 6 adventurous souls from 27-32 to adventure within and learn MUCH about the ways of combat.<br>
   If you need assistance in your quest, please feel free to ask. Although these locations are not entirely accessable to even the most savy of teleporters, it is not impossible to reach these locations with some haste. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Advanced Slayer, WurnSlayer<BR>
Assigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/22/01 1:06:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> I thank you allfor your insight and encouragement.<br>
<br>
I have visited the Giant fort in WW and was greeted with disdain.<br>
<br>
One giant did mention that I looked very similar to a wodd elf that had come throught long before. He then mentioned something rather grotesque about munching on her bones and having her for supper.<br>
<br>
This infuriated me and I did battle with him. I reigned the victor in that skirmish, but decided I should most likely leave as the other giants had turned and were looking at me in a most unpleasant way.<br>
<br>
I will repay that visit and the insult to my mother as well.<br>
<br>
Dalnir is the next place I will search for more information.<br>
Maybe she was not slain in velious. My thoughts turn to her constantly. I hope I will find her one day.<br>
<br>
Salvia Mirasdottir<br>
25th lv Druid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/28/01 12:42:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Tigonie rests quietly at her camp in Warsliks Woods.  She pokes at her campfire, then musingly eats a Batwing Crunchie.  A thought crosses her mind.  Has Salvia had any success? The Warrior has heard nothing.<br>
<br>
It would be difficult for a message runner to find Tigonie out here by herself in the woods, yet the Wood Elf appreciates the quiet and the peace of the wind in the trees...a few more days, a few more days to rest here, then the battle should be joined again.<br>
<br>
Of late, Tigonie has waxed contemplative, and has taken to these woodland wanderings. She has come to love Kunark, not as she loves Faydwer, but second best.  The trees here call to her--a different call than the trees at home, but they call, nonetheless. She glances towards her pack, which, among many things, holds the note she received from Xior.  It would be no good getting it out.  The courier who had delivered it several days ago had had to read it to her.  Xior had very much wanted her to come to Velious. She wonders whether or not she should join him.<br>
<br>
Tigonie pulls out another Batwing Crunchie and recalls her last trip there.  She was younger and she was alone, but then again, it was not very long ago.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  The wind bit mercilessly at her armor, and the snow crunched underfoot as Tigonie departed from the Igloos. It almost seemed that a trace of apprehension showed on her face as she checked again that she headed in the right direction. But her step and her demeanor were confident, belying any forebodings she may have felt. Soon icy water yawned before her. She shuddered at the thought of getting in, but there was little chance of staying dry if she intended to travel in this region. She performed a shallow dive and swam to the next island--or was it only a piece of ice? Who could tell? Her swimming had improved greatly as of late, and though the water was frigid, Tigonie took pride in her new skill and quickly reached the opposite shore. Soon she clambered up the bank and began again through the snow.<br>
<br>
&quot;I like the noise this snow makes,&quot; thought Tigonie. &quot;It is all crunchy.&quot; She checked again to make sure her direction was correct. She wondered whether she would be able to make it to Thurgadin, but the sun was bright and the day looked promising. Surely she would be just fine. One more check of direction, then Tigonie relaxed a little and began to enjoy the journey. &quot;Velious is not so bad,&quot; she thought. &quot;Even if it is rather stark, the sunlight on the snow makes such pretty sparkles!&quot;<br>
<br>
She fell into a bit of a daydream, but soon her reverie was shattered by the swipe of claws at her boot! It was one of those snow cougars again, and she knew she was outmatched, alone. Automatically, she swung her sword. Although the blade struck flesh, she knew it was vain. Tigonie ran for her life. <br>
<br>
Not knowing where to go--for the map had suddenly flown out of her head--she turned and headed back the way she had come. Tigonie struggled to keep her feet from sliding as she retraced her icy path back to the shore. The Cat at her heels had no such problem, and she could feel its hot breath upon her. Tigonie's breath came faster, as she thought wildly, &quot;Perhaps I can outswim it! Or perhaps it will not follow me into the water!&quot; She dove as far out as she could manage and used the momentum to speed herself towards the opposite shore. For a moment, the cougar seemed as though he would not follow. But, nay, the beast was a good swimmer. Faster Tigonie's arms stroked, her legs kicked, as she propelled herself through the icy deep trying to reach the first island and make it back to the igloos. The salt of the water stung her wounds, and the beast slashed again, hitting its mark. Oh! Would she never reach the shore!? The bank approached, but her limbs--her leg did not seem to kick anymore in the water. She clambered up the bank, but the Cat was upon her, and she collapsed, her wounded leg refusing to support her weight. Blackness came over her….<br>
<br>
******<br>
<br>
She awoke, feeling stiff. A kind voice said to her, &quot;Rest.&quot; She looked, and saw an Ogress leaning over her. Tigonie tried to sit up, but the world seemed to spin. Grunga--for that was the Ogress, of course, smiled. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> It was not exactly a happy memory overall. She had been thankful for Grunga's  help, but wonders how she would fare in Velious again by herself.  Tigonie takes a drink of Honey Mead, pokes at the fire again, and leans back against a comfortable tree trunk, wondering where Salvia is.<br>
<br>
/ooc Grunga is from CdL. One night I had tried to reach Thurganin by myself, and died, of course (no SoW, no invis).  Grunga logged in around the time I died and was sweet enough to get me a res. They have threatened to clear out their message board, and the story was something I had posted there.  In a moment of inspiration, I thought I'd incorporate the story here, though that was not my originial intent when I started writing. <p>Tigonie Silvanstar<br>
Warrior of the 35th Season<br>
Fourth Elder of <a href=http://www.webhazard.net>The Tears of Veeshan<a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A> at: 8/28/01 5:16:00 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/29/01 8:47:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> I sit near the corpse of a giant.  This one was younger than the rest but seemed to be most exuberant about the tales he had heard of when my mother had ventured to this fort.  The insults he hurled were of a most foul and disgusting tone.  <br>
<br>
I warned him to leave of the insults and just tell me where he had heard of the druid going to after departing here, but I guess they can't hear with their heads up so high.<br>
<br>
I take what little of value he has on him and conceal myself from the sight of his brothers.<br>
<br>
Walking to the gate of the enormous fort I decided it was time to at least explore and find out where this &quot;Crypt of Dalnir&quot; was to be found.<br>
<br>
After exploring the woods I came to a shore of a lake I had not heard of.  I walk along the shore, letting the sound of the water calm my soul of its sorrow.  <br>
<br>
Off to my right I here the sound of a skulking brute.  These giant orange ape looking creatures seem harmless enough as long as they are left unprovoked.  I follow the sound to a curious tunnel in the side of a hill.<br>
<br>
As i enter the tunnel a strange dank smell greets me, along with the hoots and howls of the brutes.  The floor is a little slippery so I transform into the shape of a wolf to take advantage of the sure purchase only claws can obtain.<br>
<br>
I follow my nose to a room with two of the brutes standing near a small pool.  Almost as if they are guarding some secret.  This thought draws my insatiable curiousity to the pool.  My wolf's nose sniffs it.  But there is no scent of water. Only the same dank smell of the tunnel.<br>
<br>
I place a paw in to test the water, and my foot slides through dryly to hard rock below the &quot;surface&quot;. <br>
&quot;This is no pool,&quot; I think to myself.<br>
<br>
I walk down under the surface of the &quot;water&quot; afraid for a moment that I may be enveloped unsuspectingly by some murky bottomless depth( I am slightly afraid of being in the water you see)<br>
<br>
But instead I have entered a tunnel and I hear a faint unfamiliar sound.<br>
<br>
As I turn a corner i am taken aback by a stench that knocks me back to my natural form and I retch.  This is the stench of death, and all around me I here the screaming of tormented souls.<br>
<br>
I suspect I have entered the crypt...<br>
<br>
Salvia Mirasdottir<br>
25th lvl druid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/17/01 11:34:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Having returned from barren, icy Velious to her beloved tree city, Tigonie carefully taps small dents from her armor, has her weapons sharpened, cleans out her packs, and does more than a dozen small things one does between battles.<br>
<br>
Musing thoughtfully among the boughs, Tigonie wonders where she should travel next.  Perhaps she should check on young Talcee, who is growing up quickly in Kunark.  Then her thoughts turn to Dalnir.  Tigonie fleetingly remembers how the slime from the floors of Dalnir never WOULD fully come off of her old bronze boots--there was always an odd haze on the soles once she had been there.  But mostly, the Warrior wonders what had happened to Salvia.  The Druid had entered the Crypt, and no one had heard from her since.... <p>Tigonie Silvanstar<br>
Warrior of the 35th Season<br>
Fourth Elder of <a href=http://www.webhazard.net>The Tears of Veeshan<a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A> at: 9/17/01 1:21:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tears of Veeshan</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/26/01 11:38:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> After my first experience at the crypt, I was loathe to return.  But a strong calling came to me in my sleep.  In my dreams i saw a vision of my mother entering the deep tunnel.<br>
<br>
She was walking proudly..unafraid of what lay ahead.  Traveling with a small band of fighters the moved deep into the crypt.  Many strange beings were encountered, and slain.  The monsters were hideous, mouths full of teeth that seemed to float in mid air, strange piles of a gooey substance that came alive with feirceness, and strangest of all were the dwarves, erudites, and dark elves that seemed under a mind control.<br>
<br>
I saw my mother snatched up in the middle of one battle by a strange lizard man.  Not an iksar, but something far stranger.<br>
<br>
The party turned after the battle and n oticed her gone.  They called her name again and again but no reply came.<br>
<br>
Ten i saw Mirahze, my beloved mother in a cell, covered in dirt and slime.  A collar was around her neck and those strange lizards were taunting her mercilessly.<br>
<br>
Then one giant of a lizard walked toward her.  he had many adornments of jewelry, satin and what looked like body marks under the skin.  he spoke a single sentence to her..<br>
<br>
&quot;You belong to the kly now,&quot; he said. Then he brought a glowing amulet to herface and laughed maniacally.<br>
<br>
I awoke in a sweat, unsure of this dream and what it meant, but i gathered my things and set off for the crypt once again.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tears of Veeshan</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/20/01 8:35:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> I have returned from the Crypt...saved by many of my brothers and sisters from the evil Kly.<br>
<br>
But I suppose I should start from the beginning...<br>
<br>
After my fitful dream I headed for the crypt of Dalnir.  Luckily my sense of direction did not misguide me this time and i arrived only a few minutes later.<br>
<br>
Again I transformed into a wolf at the mouth of the tunnel so as not to slip on the slimy floor.<br>
<br>
Again i found the cave with the large brutes gaurding their secret pool(I wonder if even they know what it is).<br>
<br>
I entered the water and began heading down into the crypt. That stench, I fear, I will never forget.  It knocked me back and back to my natural form as it had before.  <br>
<br>
I gathered my senses, calmed myself and started searching.  <br>
<br>
As i turned the corner I came face to face with the ugliest gobin I had ever seen.  Thank Tunare I had made myself invisible to their sight before I entered.  I moved forward.<br>
<br>
Inside the temple of the Kly I found a pit that leads to the second floor.  I umped down(with the help of some batwings so as not to get hurt, and explored a bit.<br>
<br>
I found a sacrificial table, a weapons room, and a couple of nasty monsters, but no cells where my mother could be. <br>
<br>
But I knew how to get to the third level, so off I went.  <br>
<br>
After a short while I came to what looked like the cell from my dream.  I looked in and....EMPTY. She wasn't there.  I became panicked.  Tears formed in my eyes, rage burned in my stomach.  My vision began to cloud....I was losing control.<br>
<br>
I closed my eyes, calmed my maddened spirit, and continued my search.<br>
<br>
I entered a great hall full of the Kly and their minions.  None of them see me(thank Tunare).  As I enter what appears to be a throne room I see many Kly gathered around a very large being...He is being referred to as &quot;Overseer&quot;.  <br>
<br>
He has turned and looked at ME!  The other Kly turn, they see me now too.  I try to run away, but there are too many of them, I can't even get any of my spells off to defend myself.<br>
<br>
Soon I am bound hand and foot, and being led back to the second floor and that table I had seen earlier.<br>
<br>
The Overseer whispers in my ear &quot;You are a fool, and now all of Norrath will fall into my grasp with just this first step!&quot;<br>
<br>
..This is where I must pause, my throat is dry, my eyes are weary....Call on me tomorrow traveleer and I shall tell you the rest of the tale.&lt;bows and waves goodbye&gt;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
