Warrior of the 36th Season<br>
Third Elder of <a href=http://www.webhazard.net>The Tears of Veeshan<a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A> at: 10/20/01 3:38:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tears of Veeshan</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/21/01 9:33:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Not sure how to do that or what changes need to be made..but I will do my best.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirahze521.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tears of Veeshan</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/24/01 3:44:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> ::Salvia steps back to the table in the inn where she began her story. She orders a drink of honey dew and a light meal of baked roots and waits for her companions to arrive::<br>
<br>
<br>
::She waves as they enter and offers them places at the table::<br>
<br>
&quot;Now where was I?&quot; she ponders a moment,&quot;Oh yes. Now I remember..&quot;<br>
<br>
And the tale begins again....<br>
<br>
The Kly had me locked up in a cage.  It was too dark to see anyway of getting out easily.  My hands had been bound so I could not transport out easily.  I was also to fatigued to form the spell words anyway. My stuggle with the Kly Oveerseer left me drained and almost unconcious.<br>
<br>
Outside the bars of my new prison a smoldering goo was left to watch me.  Every few moments it would lift a slimy eyestalk and look at me with its sickly dripping &quot;eye&quot; and then return the stalk to the rest of its slimy mass.<br>
<br>
I sat in the stinkin darkness, trying desperately to remain awake.  <br>
<br>
&quot;How do I get myself out of this one?&quot; I thought desperately.<br>
<br>
A while later I was awakened. When I had fallen asleep I do not know, but now I was being taken back up to the second level by 2 strong Kly acolytes.  By their markings I guessed they were apprentices of some arcane magic, but their physical strength revealed warrior blood in them as well.<br>
<br>
<br>
As we entered the second floors hall, the intensity of the light <br>
caused me to squint my eyes from discomfort.  It seemed as if the very walls were on fire, they had so many torches and candles lit.  It was then that I heard the calls from higher in the crypt.<br>
<br>
&quot;Salvia!! Where are you!!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Kly seemed to take no notice whatsoever and I thought I had imagined it.  Then the cries came again..many voices calling my name.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am HERE!!&quot; I shouted,&quot; They have me on the second floor!! Please hurry!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We come!!&quot; was the reply.  But I knew they must be having a hard time with the creatures that guard the entrance.  <br>
<br>
The Overseer scoffed at me and garbled something in my direction.<br>
<br>
I was placerd on a table near a pool of water.  The Overseer had an amulet in his hand that gleaamed dully in the firelight.  He walked over to the water, humming and chanting a strange song.  As he neared the pool, the water began to churn and bubble. A faint glow came from the center of the pool.  The Overseer thrust the amulet into the pool and the water hissed and churned all around it.  The light grew even more intense than the torchlight, I turned my head for fear of losing my sight to that brightness.<br>
<br>
Then all became quiet.  <br>
<br>
The Overseer lifted the amulet, which now glowed brightly from within, and began walking towards me. He lifted the amulet to my face and I screamed.<br>
<br>
The power from the amulet was ripping into my mind.  Shards of magic pierced my mind and ripped my soul to shreds.  I screamed again and again, begging for those at the entrance to hurry.  <br>
<br>
I could barely hear them now.  The last thing I remember is a quiet voice entering my mind.<br>
<br>
&quot;You must fight the magic,&quot; Ennya whispered.  How I heard her I do not know.  But alas I could not fight it, and once again the world went black.<br>
<br>
:: Salvia looks at her companions with a slight smile::<br>
<br>
&quot;You are now the ones who look tired,&quot;she says,&quot; Order more drinks and let us dine together, then I will finish my story.&quot;<br>
<br>
:: Salvia calls a waitress over and asks that her friends order some food::<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ToV Elder</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/25/01 7:23:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Tigonie thought back to the events of that day.  Salvia, so young and innocent, looking for her mother in the land of Kunark, with a hope that defied all hope, believing her mother to be alive and held captive in Dalnir.  The thought of the young Druid going into Dalnir alone seemed unthinkable.  Yet the girl was on such a mission, it seemed to be true that she had done that very thing!<br>
<br>
Tigonie and a number of others who had been in the AnDarim tavern--plus some others to whom they had dispatched messages--had grabbed their packs and headed to the evil Crypt, meeting at the enterance.  Solarianne and some others to whom they had sent messages to had not yet arrived.  Tigonie said to Rayth, &quot;I don't think we should wait. We have enough of a force here. Let the others catch up.&quot;  Rayth agreed, and together all those who had already arrived entered Dalnir--about a dozen in all.<br>
<br>
The place was as Tigonie remembered it from months before:  the slime covered floor, and the dank smell of death, and the evil creatures inhabiting it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Salvia!! Where are you!!&quot; they yelled.<br>
<br>
A faraway, almost muffeled voice replied, &quot;I am HERE!! They have me on the second floor!! Please hurry!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Tigonie shouted, &quot;We come!!&quot;  Yet there could be no haste.  A Coerced Dwarf blocked their way, with a Ravenous Nibbler nearby.  Blades flashed, and the Dwarf proved to be a worthy foe.  She healed herself even as they thought she neared death.  Death--her release from the bondage of the Kly.  Pity filled Tigonie's heart as the Dwarf let out a final cry.  Elves have no special love for Dwarves, yet she thought of this one spending her youth in the land of Faydwer.  The end of the Dwarf's life was in this foul place, and according to Mala the Wood Elves might soon share the same fate--no, that could not be!  But at least there was freedom in death.  <br>
<br>
Tigonie had little time to muse, however, as they faced the sharp teeth of a Nibbler, teeth that could pierce strong armor.  The dim-witted creature fell to their blades, and they entered the twisting hall.  Gyrating Goo, more Nibblers, Coerced Goblins, Iksar, Gnomes--servant after servant of the Kly blocked their way.  It seemed as though they would never reach Salvia.  Where would she be?  &quot;We are close!&quot; shouted Tigonie, though she was not sure of that at all.<br>
<br>
A panicked voice replied, &quot;Oh no! they are going to make me a coerced like the others here! Please anyone nearby help me!&quot;  Tigonie's stomach lurched.  It could not really be true that the Kly really <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    could</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> coerce Wood Elves, could it be?<br>
<br>
Tigonie yelled, with more confidence than she felt, &quot;Salvia, they cannot coerce Wood Elves...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Tell <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    them</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that, Tigonie. They sure are trying!  I feel a magic, strong magic. It is creeping into my brain. I'm trying to resist.  It hurts! Millions of glass shards seem to be tearing my mind to shreds...&quot;  The voice trailed off.<br>
<br>
&quot;We are coming, Salvia!&quot;  No answer.  Only the sounds of battle echoed in the dank hallway.  Would this hall <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    never</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be clear of the Kly's evil ones? <p>Tigonie Silvanstar<br>
Warrior of the 36th Season<br>
Third Elder of <a href=http://www.webhazard.net>The Tears of Veeshan<a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A> at: 10/25/01 7:27:33 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utigonie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigonie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ToV Elder</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/25/01 7:25:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Salvia's Quest</span><hr size=1> Finally, they reached the Temple.  Tigonie shouted again, &quot;Salvia?&quot;  For a moment, there was no answer, then a Wood Elf attacked!  &quot;Salvia!  What are you doing?&quot;<br>
<br>
Salvia shouted in return, &quot;Tigonie you will belong to the Kly as I do!&quot;  A spell landed on the Warrior.  Tigonie felt sick, realizing what she was going to have to do.<br>
<br>
Takhteh yelled, &quot;Dammit they've taken Salvia's mind!&quot;  Kyrael turned, boggled at Salvia, and shook her head, looking confused.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Death is the only release for her,&quot; Tigonie said, the words sticking in her throat.  <br>
<br>
Fizzlebang shouted, &quot;There must be another way.&quot; But Tigonie knew there was no other way for the Kly's servants.  In any case, it was certain that Salvia intended to attack until she was either victorious or perished.<br>
<br>
Nathanius cried out desperately, &quot;Rayth can't you alter her memory?&quot;  Tigonie hesitated.  The young Druid had not been able to root the Warrior, and had suffered much from the Warrior's blows.  <br>
<br>
Nearing death, the Druid's eyes cleared and she looked like herself for a fleeting second as she begged, &quot;You have to kill me. It's the only way. Please kill me.&quot;  Salvia's face looked so pained in that moment.  Tigonie's heart seemed to stop beating, her soul pierced by the thought of what she had to do.  Her sword came down once more, and Salvia uttered a piteous cry.  Tigonie thought she had heard her whisper, &quot;Thank you,&quot; as she breathed her last.<br>
<br>
Tignonie and the others lowered their heads and mourned the loss of Salvia.  Fizzlebang shouted, &quot;All that is left now is revenge!&quot;  <br>
<br>
Wahoombah said, &quot;Aye, mefinks dis be war. Fer da gloree af Rallos Zek!&quot;  <br>
<br>
Fizzlebang exclaimed, &quot;Aye! Let the flames of Solusek Ro consume this foul place!&quot; <br>
<br>
Anger welled up in Tigonie, also.  She looked at her young friend, a coersion implant visible in her skin.  Tigonie reached down and removed the evil thing from the Druid's arm.  <br>
<br>
As the others clammored for revenge, Kyrael said quietly, &quot;But it is not a cleric's job to leave the dead to rest.  May I pray for her return?&quot;<br>
<br>
Rayth asked, &quot;Can you attempt to being her back, Kyrael, and cleanse her soul?&quot;<br>
<br>
Tigonie nodded and said, &quot;Please try, Kyrael.&quot;  Fizzlebang shuddered at the thought, in case Salvia might not be cured.  <br>
<br>
Kyrael prayed, and minutes passed, but nothing happened.  The Cleric said, &quot;No response. It is almost as though her soul is hiding.&quot;<br>
<br>
Fizzlebang sugested timidly, &quot;Perhaps it was consumed?&quot;<br>
<br>
Nathanius glanced at Tigonie's striken face and said, &quot;Try again Kyr!&quot;  Kyrael nodded at Nate and returned to her prayers.  Nathanius bowed down and prayed also.<br>
<br>
In grief, Tigonie shouted, &quot;Surely the Kly is not so powerful!&quot;<br>
<br>
But then, the Druid seemed to stir.  She looked around weakly.  &quot;What is going on?&quot;<br>
<br>
Tignoe shouted with joy, &quot;Thank you, Kyrael!  You have resurrected her and brought her back to us!&quot;<br>
<br>
Kyrael replied with a look of relief, &quot;Just doing my job.&quot; &lt;cough&gt;<br>
<br>
Tigonie said, &quot;Salvia, you were coerced by the Kly and we thought we could not resurrect you.&quot;  They all gathered around the Druid, hugging her and weeping tears of joy.<br>
<br>
Salvia looked at Tigonie, completely puzzled.  &quot;The last thing I remember, I was entering the Crypt.&quot;<br>
<br>
